OL,6,FHe added: "The standard of proof
OL,7,Fneeded for a criminal prosecution is
OL,8,Fhigh. For a conviction, the
OL,9,Fprosecution must establish beyond a
OL,10,Freasonable doubt, through admissible
OL,11,Fevidence, the commission of a criminal
OL,12,Foffence by an identified suspect.
OL,14,F"These two cases were individually
OL,15,Fconsidered by two experienced
OL,16,Fprosecution teams. It has been
OL,17,Fdetermined that the available evidence
OL,18,Fin both cases is insufficient to
OL,19,Fprovide a reasonable prospect of
OL,20,Fconviction.
