OL,6,FIn a statement, the PPS added: "In the
OL,7,Fcase of William McGreanery,
OL,8,Fprosecutors were satisfied that the
OL,9,Favailable evidence was capable of
OL,10,Fproving that Mr McGreanery was unarmed
OL,11,Fand presented no threat to any soldier.
OL,13,F"However, the admissible evidence was
OL,14,Finsufficient to prove that the
OL,15,Freported suspect was the soldier known
OL,16,Fas Soldier A who was responsible for
OL,17,Fcausing Mr McGreanery's death.
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G6/9
