OL,6,F"In the case of Annette McGavigan, who
OL,7,Fwas entirely innocent, prosecutors
OL,8,Fcould notJprove that the reported
OL,9,Fsuspect fired the shots that killed
OL,10,Fthe teenager.
OL,12,F"It also could not be disproved that
OL,13,Fthe shots may have been aimed at a
OL,14,Fgunman that someJwitnesses reported
OL,15,Fseeing, and were therefore fired in
OL,16,Flawful self-defence."
