OL,6,FMr Hardy said: "We recognise that
OL,7,Fthese decisions not to prosecute will
OL,8,Fbe deeply disappointing to the
OL,9,Fvictims' families who lost their loved
OL,10,Fone in very painful circumstances and
OL,11,Fare understandably still seeking
OL,12,Fclarity on what happened.
OL,14,F"We have today written to them to
OL,15,Fexplain the detailed reasons for the
OL,16,Fdecisions and have offered meetings to
OL,17,Fgive any further explanation they may
OL,18,Frequire about the basis of these
OL,19,Fdecisions.
